%N A397569 a(1) = 1; for n >= 2, a(n) is the smallest number whose Hamming distance from a(n-1) is Fibonacci(n)).
%e A397569 a(2) = 1 = 1_2. The smallest number at Hamming distance F(3) = 2 from 1 flips its 1-bit and the lowest 0-bit, giving 10_2 = 2 = a(3).
%o A397569 (Python)
%o A397569 a, x, y = 0, 1, 2
%o A397569 for n in range(1,13):
%o A397569    a ^= (1 << x) - 1
%o A397569    print(a)
%o A397569    x, y = y, x+y
